This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method to personalize RNN models for session-based recommendations. It also involves the use of Recurrent Neural Networks, which is a popular machine learning technique. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as session-based recommendations are often used in e-commerce and video streaming services, which involve information retrieval. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves natural language processing techniques to process user session data. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a method to improve the performance of recommendation systems using machine learning techniques. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper involves industry datasets, which may have security and privacy concerns.
